  "storyline": "# Storyline\n\n## Context\n\nT20 match outcomes shift ball by ball with match state (overs, wickets, run-rate); flat match-level stats miss this in-game movement.\n\n## Workflow\n\nPhase-level EDA → ball-by-ball match-state feature engineering → win-probability classification → Elo-style team-rating layer.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n- **EDA:** phase-level analysis (Powerplay/Middle/Death) with Pandas, surfacing scoring patterns consistent with public T20 research.\n- **Features:** 25+ ball-by-ball match-state features across team composition, player metrics, venue and conditions.\n- **Win-probability modeling:** Random Forest, Logistic Regression and SVM predicting win probability; Random Forest best at ~80%.\n- **Elo-style ratings:** a long-term team-strength layer contextualizing live win-probability estimates.\n\n## Outcomes\n\nProduced ball-by-ball win-probability estimates with an Elo-style long-term rating layer, framed for cricket-domain audiences."
